		<paragraph x="0" y="+0" width="407" height="0" style="normal" tabs="" indent="0"><![CDATA[<TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="13" COLOR="#0000FF" LETTERSPACING="0" KERNING="0"><B>In:</B><FONT COLOR="#000000"> It is the correct answer.</FONT></FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT><TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="13" COLOR="#000000" LETTERSPACING="0" KERNING="0"><B>Until:</B> The chart doesn't include figures for years before 1804.</FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT><TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="13" COLOR="#000000" LETTERSPACING="0" KERNING="0"><B>Since:</B> The tense of the main verb in this sentence is past simple. 'Since' is not suitable here.</FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT><TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="13" COLOR="#000000" LETTERSPACING="0" KERNING="0"><B>From:</B> 'From' is used to refer to the beginning of a period, but this sentence refers to one particular point in time â€“ 1804.</FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT>]]></paragraph>
