		<paragraph x="0" y="+0" width="407" height="0" style="normal" tabs="" indent="0"><![CDATA[<TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="13" COLOR="#0000FF" LETTERSPACING="0" KERNING="0"><B>increases:</B><FONT COLOR="#000000"> It is the correct answer.</FONT></FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT><TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="13" COLOR="#000000" LETTERSPACING="0" KERNING="0"><B>fluctuations:</B> 'Fluctuation' means 'ups and downs', in other words no steady trend in either direction.</FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT><TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="13" COLOR="#000000" LETTERSPACING="0" KERNING="0"><B>decreases:</B> Check the table again. 'Developing regions' means those countries which are still developing. In the table, these are referred to as 'Less developed regions.' What changes are predicted for these regions?</FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT><TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="13" COLOR="#000000" LETTERSPACING="0" KERNING="0"><B>percentages:</B> Neither the table nor the chart refers to percentages.</FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT>]]></paragraph>
